<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1735,1797]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">
The genus was not revised and has seven recognized species (
<bibRefCitation author="Krajcik, M." box="[893,1066,1735,1762]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref26604" refString="Krajcik, M. (2008 b) Cetoniidae of the World. Catalogue - Part II. (Coleoptera: Scarabaeoidea). Animma. x, Supplement, 1 - 72 + I - XXIII." type="book chapter" year="2008">Krajcik 2008b</bibRefCitation>
). The species of this genus are myrmecophilous. There is only one species recorded for 
<collectingCountry box="[788,953,1771,1797]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Guinea-Bissau</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Janson, O. E." box="[967,1112,1771,1797]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref26313" refString="Janson, O. E. (1907) List of the Cetoniidae collected by the late Leonardo Fea in West Africa. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, Serie 3, 3 (43) 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="1907">Janson 1907</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
